"received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2020-05-24T14:34:18Z", "updated_at": "2020-05-24T19:17:30Z", "closed_at": "2020-05-24T19:17:25Z", "author_association": "OWNER", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/pulls/63", "html_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/63", "diff_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/63.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/63.patch", "merged_at": "2020-05-24T19:17:25Z"}, "body": "When you ask for request `stats`, the order of requests is not preserved because we do a group of reports. This PR preserves this order for better usability. ", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/63/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/63/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/61", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/61/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/61/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/61/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/61", "id": 623700350, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDIyMzAwMTc0", "number": 61, "title": "Fix concurrency and iterations parameters", "user": {"login": "fcsonline", "id": 135988, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTk4OA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/135988?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline", "html_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-05-23T17:02:18Z", "updated_at": "2020-08-06T16:21:33Z", "closed_at": "2020-08-06T16:21:29Z", "author_association": "OWNER", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/pulls/61", "html_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/61", "diff_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/61.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/61.patch", "merged_at": "2020-08-06T16:21:29Z"}, "body": "Since we introduced `async`, the concurrency model of drill has changed a bit. The number of threads is less important. Also, in this PR \r\nhttps://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/55, we introduced a new parameter to choose how many concurrent iterations we wanted to execute at the same time, but this number was affecting the total number of requests was going to execute `drill` in total. For this reason, I wanted to simplify all this and achieve a place where:\r\n- The user only choose the number of iteration to be executed. `iterations` parameter\r\n- Number of concurrent iterations during the tests. `concurrency` parameter\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes all this.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, this PR also computes the duration of the test only during the futures resolutions and not counting the preparation (building the futures). This is a more realistic number of requests per second a server can handle.\r\n\r\n**Pending tasks:**\r\n\r\n- [x] The pool of clients need to be fixed to be shared between futures to achieve keep alive\r\n- [x] Bug: Requests take longer than expected because meanwhile a response is processes a new request start to fill up the concurrency pool. Try to fix it.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/61/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/61/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/60", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/60/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/60/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/fcsonline/drill/issues/60/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline/drill/pull/60", "id": 622619533, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDIxNDUwMTA2", "number": 60, "title": "Handle better misconfiguration", "user": {"login": "fcsonline", "id": 135988, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTk4OA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/135988?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline", "html_url": "https://github.com/fcsonline", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fcsonline/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "